# Netlify Deployment Ready ✅

Your portfolio is now organized and ready for deployment!

## Current Structure (Production-Ready):
```
Portfolio/
├── index.html         # Main portfolio page
├── blog.html          # Blog page with Medium integration
├── assets/            # All images and media
├── css/               # All stylesheets
├── data/              # Medium posts configuration
├── js/                # All JavaScript files
└── docs/              # Documentation and non-production files
```

## To Deploy on Netlify:

### Option 1: Drag & Drop
1. Select all these files/folders:
   - index.html
   - blog.html
   - assets/
   - css/
   - data/
   - js/
2. Drag them to app.netlify.com

### Option 2: Git Deploy (Recommended)
1. Commit these changes:
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "Reorganize for Netlify deployment"
   git push
   ```
2. Connect your GitHub repo to Netlify
3. Auto-deploys on every push

## Files Moved to docs/ (Not Needed for Production):
- All markdown files (.md)
- LaTeX files (.tex)
- Old blog posts
- Resume files
- Development documentation
- Backup folders

## Important:
- All paths have been updated to work from root
- Your Medium posts configuration is in data/medium-posts.json
- Blog now shows your Medium articles with proper links